<p><b>What is entrepreneurship according to Fajardo?</b>  To Schumpeter as cited by Fajardo(1994), an entrepreneur is an innovator. He does new things in a new way. He supplies new products, makes new techniques of production; discovers new markets and develops new sources of raw materials.</p>
<p><b>Who is an entrepreneur pdf notes?</b> Document Information. An entrepreneur is defined as someone who innovates, raises money, assembles resources, hires managers, and launches a business to fulfill economic opportunities. Entrepreneurship involves the process of starting a new business through innovation and risk-taking.</p>
